parent_desc: Encourage your child to create a food chart and record their daily meals for the week.
child_desc: Hi _______, please create a food chart and write down everything you eat for each meal every day. This way, you can keep track of what you are eating and learn more about your food choices. Its a great way to become more aware of your dietary habits (that is how much junk food vs healthy food you are consuming) and make healthier decisions.
purpose_outcome: This activity promotes awareness of dietary habits and encourages healthy eating practices. By documenting their meals, your child will gain insight into their food choices

purpose_outcome: Improves vocabulary and spellings

title: Draw and Paint
parent_desc: Your child will make a collage using dried leaves/twigs and flowers that they collect themselves
purpose_outcome: This activity encourages exploration and enhances their creativity.

title: Collage
parent_desc: Your child will draw/ paint a small picture using their non dominant hand
purpose_outcome: improves focus and sharpens brain function

title: Draw and Paint
parent_desc: Your child will draw/ paint a small picture using their non dominant hand
purpose_outcome: improves focus and sharpens brain function

title: Jogging time
parent_desc: Go with your child for a short jog in the neighbourhood. Later ask child to draw a picture of what he/ she observed. This picture should have at least 7-8 elements that they saw
purpose_outcome: This activity enhances observation skills and encourages attention to detail.

title: Family Calendar
parent_desc: Your child will take charge of crafting a family calendar to coordinate activities for all family members, ensuring everyone enjoys quality time together.
child_desc: Hi ______ you will be in charge of creating a family calendar. Organize the schedules of all family members in a common calendar so you can understand when you guys can spend quality time together. Be creative you can include holidays, birthdays or other events where you all can spend time together.
purpose_outcome: This activity will help your child develop interpersonal intelligence through collaboration and understanding everyones needs. This will also help develop

title: Study Planner
parent_desc: Your child will create a weekly study plan or schedule to help them organize their learning goals and tasks effectively.
child_desc: Hi _____, create a weekly study schedule where you plan what subjects you need to study, any homework assignments, and any other tasks you need to complete. This will help you stay on track and make sure you have enough time for everything. you need to complete. This will help you stay on track and make sure you have enough time for everything. Following Study plan on regular basis will help you to reflect back on strategy and make changes
purpose_outcome: This task will help them develop goal setting, organizational, and time management skills.

title: Meal Tracker
parent_desc: Encourage your child to create a food chart and record their daily meals for the week.
child_desc: Hi _______, please create a food chart and write down everything you eat for each meal every day. This way, you can keep track of what you are eating and learn more about your food choices. Its a great way to become more aware of your dietary habits (that is how much junk food vs healthy food you are consuming) and make healthier decisions.
purpose_outcome: This activity promotes awareness of dietary habits and encourages healthy eating practices. By documenting their meals, your child will gain insight into their food choices

title: Emotions Charades
parent_desc: Your family will engage in a game to explore how tone influences communication and emotions. Through this activity, you will learn how the way you speak affects how others understand you and perceive your emotions.
child_desc: This activity helps you see if your child can express emotions well and understand how others feel.
purpose_outcome: Hi _____, play a game with your family on how the tone odour voices affects, how others understand our emotions. This activity is all about understanding how someone feels just by the way they say a sentence.

title: Financial Literacy
parent_desc: Your child will maintain a spending journal for a week. They will note down every purchase they make, along with how much they spend.
child_desc: Hi _______, maintain an EXPENSE TRACKER ( spending journal ) for one week, writing down every purchase you make along with the amount spent. Categorize items in WANTs Vs NEEDS, and reflect back.
purpose_outcome: This activity promotes financial awareness and responsibility.

title: Family Calendar
parent_desc: Your child will take charge of crafting a family calendar to coordinate activities for all family members, ensuring everyone enjoys quality time together.
child_desc: Hi ______ you will be in charge of creating a family calendar. Organize the schedules of all family members in a common calendar so you can understand when you guys can spend quality time together. Be creative you can include holidays, birthdays or other events where you all can spend time together.

title: Study Planner
parent_desc: Your child will create a weekly study plan or schedule to help them organize their learning goals and tasks effectively.
child_desc: Hi _____, create a weekly study schedule where you plan what subjects you need to study, any homework assignments, and any other tasks you need to complete. This will help you stay on track and make sure you have enough time for everything. you need to complete. This will help you stay on track and make sure you have enough time for everything. Following Study plan on regular basis will help you to reflect back on strategy and make changes
purpose_outcome: This task will help them develop goal setting, organizational, and time management skills.

title: Tune your Ears
parent_desc: Every evening, have your kid recite shubhamkaroti shloka and then touch the feet of the elderly in the house to take blessings
purpose_outcome: Understanding the concept of volume

title: Meal Tracker
parent_desc: Encourage your child to create a food chart and record their daily meals for the week.
child_desc: Hi _______, please create a food chart and write down everything you eat for each meal every day. This way, you can keep track of what you are eating and learn more about your food choices. Its a great way to become more aware of your dietary habits (that is how much junk food vs healthy food you are consuming) and make healthier decisions.
purpose_outcome: This activity promotes awareness of dietary habits and encourages healthy eating practices. By documenting their meals, your child will gain insight into their food choices

title: Emotions Charades
parent_desc: Your family will engage in a game to explore how tone influences communication and emotions. Through this activity, you will learn how the way you speak affects how others understand you and perceive your emotions.
child_desc: This activity helps you see if your child can express emotions well and understand how others feel.
purpose_outcome: Hi _____, play a game with your family on how the tone odour voices affects, how others understand our emotions. This activity is all about understanding how someone feels just by the way they say a sentence.

title: Financial Literacy
parent_desc: Your child will maintain a spending journal for a week. They will note down every purchase they make, along with how much they spend.
child_desc: Hi _______, maintain an EXPENSE TRACKER ( spending journal ) for one week, writing down every purchase you make along with the amount spent. Categorize items in WANTs Vs NEEDS, and reflect back.
purpose_outcome: This activity promotes financial awareness and responsibility.
